Summary
=======
x11-touch-mouse is a utility to transform touch screen events into simulated
X11 mouse events. It is intended for use on Kobo eReaders running X11 in an
Alpine Linux chroot.

Usage:
   x11-touch-mouse [--grab] [--turn] [--flipx] [--flipy] /dev/input/eventX
     --grab  grab the device for exclusive access
     --turn  switch x and y-axis, when the coordinates of the touch device and
             the screen have a different orientation
     --flipx flip the x-axis, when the touch device and the screen have a
             different origin for x (left/right)
     --flipy flip the y-axis, when the touch device and the screen have a
             different origin for y (top/bottom)
     /dev/input/eventX
             the input device, replace X with the appropriate number

x11-touch-mouse needs to run as root to be able to read the
device.

For more information, see the x11-touch-mouse(1) man page.

